				<name type="primary" sortindex="15" value="コリントコンストラクション (Corinth Construction)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#169;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#183;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#167;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179; (Corinth Construction) is a Japanese dexterity game. The designer says &amp;quot;This game is customizable pinball, where you build the common board and launch balls of different materials (glass, wood, iron). Who earns best points?&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the game, the players begin by placing the components of a wooden pinball machine. The device does not have paddles to keep the ball in play. Instead, the game more closely resembles a pachinko machine, which are very popular in Japan. The ball falls freely after it is fired.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The flat area of the board has regular pinholes, and players start by placing pegs and barriers as they wish. Then they take turns firing a ball into the area. The base of the device has a series of slots with different scoring values. The players are trying to get the different types of pinball to fall to the more valuable slots to win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game includes a metal, magnetised peg. When the steel ball is fired, if it strikes the peg, it might stick there.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;'Corinth' is the name in Japan for this style of children's toy, from which pachinko machines developed.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
